com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class CleanTableRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianObjectRequest
        • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.CleanTableRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SiperianObjectUidProvider, Serializable

    public class CleanTableRequest
extends SiperianObjectRequest
    Represents a request object to remove all data from an Operational Reference Store (ORS) table and all its companion tables.

    Note: When you clean a parent base object, if any of its child base object is not cleaned or has data, the CleanTableRequest object fails.

    Usage Example

    CleanTableRequest request = new CleanTableRequest();
    request.setSiperianObjectUid("BASE_OBJECT.C_PARTY");
    request.isCleanStaging(true);
    request.isUseTruncate(true);
    CleanTableResponse response = (CleanTableResponse)sipClient.process(request);
    See Also:
    CleanTableResponse, SiperianObjectRequest, SiperianObjectUidProvider, Serialized Form

    API Pair: CleanTableResponse

    • Method Detail

      • isCleanStaging

        public boolean isCleanStaging()
        Indicates whether to remove rows in the staging tables and the dependent tables, such as [Staging Table]_CL, [Staging Table]_DLT, [Staging Table]_RAW, [Staging Table]_REJ, [Staging Table]_OPL, and [Staging Table]_PRL.

        Returns:
        • True to remove the rows in the staging tables and the dependent tables.
        • False to retain the rows in the staging tables and the dependent tables.

      • setCleanStaging

        public void setCleanStaging(boolean cleanStaging)
        Sets the status to indicate whether to remove rows in the staging tables and the dependent tables, such as [Staging Table]_CL, [Staging Table]_DLT, [Staging Table]_RAW, [Staging Table]_REJ, [Staging Table]_OPL, and [Staging Table]_PRL.

        Parameters:
        cleanStaging - Indicates whether to remove rows in the staging tables and the dependent tables. Specify true to remove the rows, or specify false to retain the rows in the staging tables and the dependent tables. Default is true.

      • isUseTruncate

        public boolean isUseTruncate()
        Indicates whether to use the TRUNCATE or DELETE statement to remove the records.

        Returns:
        • True to use the TRUNCATE statement.
        • False to use the DELETE statement.

      • setUseTruncate

        public void setUseTruncate(boolean isUseTruncate)
        Sets the status to indicate whether to use the TRUNCATE or DELETE statement to remove the records. The TRUNCATE statement functions faster than the DELETE statement, but the TRUNCATE statement commits transactions that might cause errors.

        Parameters:
        isUseTruncate - Indicates whether to use the TRUNCATE or DELETE statement to remove the records. Specify true to use the TRUNCATE statement, or specify false to use the DELETE statement. Default is false.

      • getTransactionAttributeType

        public TransactionAttributeType getTransactionAttributeType()
        Gets the type of the transaction attribute that specifies whether this request object can participate in the transactions. Used internally by the MDM Hub to determine the transactional capabilities of a request.

          Overrides:
          getTransactionAttributeType in class SiperianRequest
          Returns:
        • NOT_SUPPORTED if the request cannot participate in the transactions.
        • SUPPORTS if the request can participate in the transactions.
        • REQUIRED if the request requires a transaction.
        • REQUIRES_NEW if the request requires a new transaction.
